description: {"blocks":[{"key":"ad55p","text":"Staining procedure for cells analyzed by time of flight mass cytometry.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

status.info: We use this protocol and it's working

steps.step: {"blocks":[{"key":"8j470","text":"Cells are then fixed using 2% PFA, for 20mins.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"fqcn3","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"b2fhn","text":"For intracellular staining, cells are permeabilized by incubation with Triton X 0.1% for 5 min at room temperature, followed by incubation with intracellular antibody cocktail for 30 min at 4 °C.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"djflo","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"8o8vb","text":"Cells from separate donors or conditions are stained separately with Cisplatin (Cat. No. 201064, Fluidigm) followed by barcoding using the Cell-ID 20-Plex Pd Barcoding Kit (Cat. No. 201060, Fluidigm). ","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"33g17","text":"Following barcoding, samples are combined into a single 5 mL polystyrene U-bottom tube and incubated in the surface marker antibody cocktail for 30 min at 4 °C","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"9mft","text":"Stained cells are incubated overnight with Cell-ID Intercalator (Cat. No. 201192A, Fluidigm).","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"dahen","text":"The following morning, cells are washed in either Maxpar PBS (Cat. No. 201058, Fluidigm), Maxpar Cell Staining Buffer (Cat. No. 201068, Fluidigm), or Millipure Water, with a spin at 1600 RPM for 4 min to remove the supernatant and replace it with fresh buffer.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"33hi4","text":"Samples are run on a time of flight mass cytometer (CyTOF 2, Fluidigm) and analyzed with Cytobank (Cytobank Inc., RRID:SCR_014043) and Astrolabe Diagnostics (https://astrolabediagnostics.com/)","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[{"key":0,"offset":158,"length":33}],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{"0":{"type":"link","mutability":"MUTABLE","data":{"guid":"AEE09E869D6C11ECBBD20A58A9FEAC02","url":"https://astrolabediagnostics.com"}}}}

title: Time of flight mass cytometry (CyTOF)
